NOTE: The following is a template for the `.env` file that you should create in your project directory. 
This file will store sensitive information such as API keys and endpoints securely, allowing your application 
to access them without hardcoding them into your source code.

In this project, i have directly used the keys in the code, so please include them in the .env file.
# --- .env ---
# Azure OpenAI Configuration
AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY=your_azure_openai_api_key_here
AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://your_azure_openai_endpoint_here/
AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=your_deployment_name_here                  
AZURE_OPENAI_EMBEDDING_DEPLOYMENT_NAME=your_embedding_deployment_name_here

# LangChain Configuration
LANGCHAIN_API_KEY=your_langchain_api_key_here
LANGCHAIN_API_BASE_URL=https://api.langchain.com/v1 
# Observability Configuration
OBSERVABILITY_API_KEY=your_observability_api_key_here
OBSERVABILITY_API_BASE_URL=https://api.observability.com/v1
# --- End of .env ---
